com.google.android.exoplayer.chunk

Class MediaChunk

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.android.exoplayer.chunk.Chunk
      • com.google.android.exoplayer.chunk.MediaChunk
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Loader.Loadable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Mp4MediaChunk, SingleSampleMediaChunk, WebmMediaChunk

    public abstract class MediaChunk
extends Chunk
    An abstract base class for Chunks that contain media samples.

          Format format,
          int trigger,
          long startTimeUs,
          long endTimeUs,
          int nextChunkIndex)
        Constructor for a chunk of media samples.
        Parameters:
        dataSource - A DataSource for loading the data.
        dataSpec - Defines the data to be loaded.
        format - The format of the stream to which this chunk belongs.
        trigger - The reason for this chunk being selected.
        startTimeUs - The start time of the media contained by the chunk, in microseconds.
        endTimeUs - The end time of the media contained by the chunk, in microseconds.
        nextChunkIndex - The index of the next chunk, or -1 if this is the last chunk.

      • seekTo

        public abstract boolean seekTo(long positionUs,
             boolean allowNoop)
        Seeks to the specified position within the chunk.
        Parameters:
        positionUs - The desired seek time in microseconds.
        allowNoop - True if the seek is allowed to do nothing if the result is more accurate than seeking to a key frame. Always pass false if it is required that the next sample be a key frame.
        Returns:
        True if the seek results in a discontinuity in the sequence of samples returned by read(SampleHolder). False otherwise.

      • prepare

        public abstract boolean prepare()
                         throws ParserException
        Prepares the chunk for reading. Does nothing if the chunk is already prepared.

        Preparation may require consuming some of the chunk. If the data is not yet available then this method will return false rather than block. The method can be called repeatedly until the return value indicates success.

        Returns:
        True if the chunk was prepared. False otherwise.
        Throws:
        ParserException - If an error occurs parsing the media data.

      • sampleAvailable

        public abstract boolean sampleAvailable()
                                 throws ParserException
        Returns whether the next sample is available.
        Returns:
        True if the next sample is available for reading. False otherwise.
        Throws:
        ParserException

      • read

        public abstract boolean read(SampleHolder holder)
                      throws ParserException
        Reads the next media sample from the chunk.

        Should only be called after the chunk has been successfully prepared.

        Parameters:
        holder - A holder to store the read sample.
        Returns:
        True if a sample was read. False if more data is still required.
        Throws:
        ParserException - If an error occurs parsing the media data.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If called before Chunk.init(com.google.android.exoplayer.upstream.Allocator), or after Chunk.release()
